Adjust rack to middle position (middle and top positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Lightly oil a #baking sheet{}. Wash and dry all produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ¼-inch-thick rounds. (TIP: Cutting your potatoes into thin, uniform slices here is key! This will help them all roast at the same pace.) Cut @Broccoli Florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary.

In a #large bowl{}, toss potatoes with @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon}, @Cooking Oil{2%tablespoon} (4 TBSP for 4 servings), and a couple big pinches of @salt{} and @pepper{} until thoroughly coated.

Arrange potatoes on one side of prepared #baking sheet{} in a single overlapping layer (for 4, spread potatoes out across entire sheet). TIP: Be sure to shingle the potatoes in a single layer so they cook evenly.

Evenly sprinkle potatoes with @Italian Cheese Blend{1/2%cup}. Add @Italian Pork Sausage{9%ounce} to empty side of same baking sheet. (For 4, add sausage to a second baking sheet; roast on top rack.)

Roast on middle rack for ~{20-25%minutes} total (you'll add broccoli to the baking sheet after ~{5%minutes}).

Meanwhile, in bowl used to season potatoes, toss broccoli with a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{}, salt, and pepper.

Once potatoes and sausage have roasted ~{5%minutes}, remove from oven and carefully add broccoli to same baking sheet. (For 4 servings, add broccoli to baking sheet with sausage.)

Return to middle rack until sausage is cooked through, potatoes are golden brown, and broccoli is tender and lightly browned, ~{15-20%minutes} more.

Transfer roasted sausage to a #cutting board{}. Once cool enough to handle, slice on a diagonal into bite-size pieces.

> If you prefer, feel free to skip the slicing.

== Dijonnaise ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} with as much @Dijon Mustard{2%teaspoon} as you like (start with half and add more if you like things spicy). Stir in @Sugar{1/4%teaspoon} (½ tsp for 4 servings). Season with salt and pepper.

Divide sausage, broccoli, and cheesy potatoes between plates. Serve with Dijonnaise on the side for dipping.